					<description><!--[CDATA[<p-->JACKSONVILLE, Fla. — A new multicenter study led by Mayo Clinic researchers has established a practical, evidence-based definition for rapidly progressive dementia (RPD), a rare but devastating form of cognitive decline that develops over months instead of years. The findings, published in Neurology, the medical journal of the American Academy of Neurology, may help clinicians […]<p></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/discussion/new-mayo-led-study-establishes-practical-definition-for-rapidly-progressive-dementia/">New Mayo-led study establishes practical definition for rapidly progressive dementia</a> appeared first on <a href="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org">Mayo Clinic News Network</a>.</p>
